# Cloudflare Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to Cloudflare Pages dashboard under Settings > Environment Variables

# =============================================================================
# FRONTEND (Required for React app)
# =============================================================================

# Clerk Authentication (Required)
# Get from: https://dashboard.clerk.com
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# =============================================================================
# BACKEND / PAGES FUNCTIONS (Required for API routes)
# =============================================================================

# Clerk Secret Key (Required for auth verification)
# Get from: https://dashboard.clerk.com under API Keys
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# RAG Service URL (Required)
# Point to your deployed RAG service (Railway, Render, or external)
RAG_SERVICE_URL=https://your-rag-service.railway.app

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL - CLOUDFLARE SERVICES
# =============================================================================

# These are configured via wrangler.toml bindings, not env vars:
# - CACHE (KV Namespace for caching API responses)
# - DB (D1 Database for user profiles and metadata)
# - VECTORIZE (Vector database for embeddings)
# - DOCUMENTS (R2 Bucket for file storage)

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================

# How to set these in Cloudflare:
# 1. Go to: https://dash.cloudflare.com
# 2. Navigate to: Pages > Your Project > Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Add variables for both Production and Preview environments
# 4. Click "Save"
# 5. Redeploy for changes to take effect

# Production vs Preview:
# - Use different Clerk keys for prod vs preview
# - Use different RAG service URLs for testing
# - Preview: pk_test_xxx / sk_test_xxx
# - Production: pk_live_xxx / sk_live_xxx
